🏗️ Lab Overview

RDPClient → Windows/Linux machine to test web/db access

LB1/LB2 → HAProxy/Keepalived for load balancing web traffic

Web1/2/3 → Apache/Nginx hosting a sample app (like a PHP app)

DB1/2/3 → MySQL-compatible HA DB (use Percona XtraDB Cluster instead of MariaDB Galera, as Percona is stable and supported on CentOS Stream 10)

Monitoring → Prometheus + Grafana (or Nagios for simplicity)

VIP → Virtual IP managed by Keepalived for HA
